Name: Rymes with Orange
rawData:
Rymes with Orange is a Canadian alternative rock band which formed in 1991 in Vancouver, British Columbia, Canada. This independent band have released four albums: Peel (1992), Trapped in the Machine (1994), Crash (1999) and One More Mile (2003). They have had three Top 10 singles on Canadian Rock Radio, with sales of over 70,000 units worldwide, and have toured Canada, New Zealand, the U.S. and the U.K., all while maintaining independent status.
The band originated in the early 1990s in Prince George, British Columbia, as The Night Watchmen, by original drummer and songwriter Alex (Julien) Dias, and writing partner, guitarist Rob Lulic. Vancouver based keyboardist Bob D'Eith later joined the band. It was when lead singer Jimmy Gilmore, subsequently a member of The Silencers from Scotland, decided to leave the band to go back to Scotland, Dias, Lulic and D'Eith continued, with what would eventually become Rymes with Orange.
In 1991, after The Night Watchmen split-up, Dias, Lulic and D'Eith joined up with UK-born lead singer Lyndon Johnson, to form Rymes With Orange in Vancouver. As The Night Watchmen, the band had a more conventional alternative rock sound, while as Rymes With Orange, their style evolved more towards a Madchester-influenced dance rock alternative rock sound.

Labels: RWO Records, Citrus Soul with A&M Distribution
